review_blob: Looks like a lager, smells like a lager, actually has some bitterness and even hop flavour. Not bad for a lager, but not really my style.
Beautiful amber with thin head. Caramel on the nose and the taste follows with more of the same. Nice bitterness. Good drink
Toffee on the nose. Beautiful copper colour with thin head. Full malt flavours, toffee, coffee and chocolate. Good bitterness keeps it refreshing. Lovely

Bottle thanks to Jaco. Pours a beautiful dark brown with large cream head that eventually recedes to a thin layer that persists. Not much aroma, slightly fruity. Taste of coffee and dark fruit, very drinkable for a 9% beer, a very smooth alcohol flavour. Really nice.
Pours a muddy orange, not much on the nose. Nice bitterness with a slight hop flavour. Enjoyable enough.
Light malt aromas. Sweet, fruity with a spicy back bone. The alcohol is very noticeable but enjoyable.
Light malty sweetness on the nose. Clear red with thick head that sticks around. Huge malty sweetness with a nice bitterness. Roasted fruit and caramel. Beautiful.
Berries on the nose, light malt sweetness. Amber with a thin head. Nice malty sweetness, with a good fruity overtone. Quite thin bodied and dry in the finish. Nice.
Litchi and citrus on the nose. Lovely dark amber with thin head. Low flavour, fruity with not much malt. Thin bodied and quite dry. Not terrible, but not really what I consider an English ale.
Sharp Roast on the nose, pours dark brown, almost black. Thin head. Flavours of roast, toffee, coffee & chocolate. Smooth and delicious
Citrus and flowers on the nose, beautiful clear amber with thin head. Slight citrus flavour with light caramel, good bitterness. This definitely tastes like more.
Slight citrus in the aroma. Clear amber with thin head. Slight spice with good caramel flavours, ends with a strong bitterness. Delicious!
Aroma of toffee & malt. Dark amber with very thin head. Huge malt flavour with slight spice, sherry like. thick body with low carbonation. Very enjoyable.

Oak in the aroma, Champaign, farm house. Minimal head, Crystal clear! Extra Sharp, slight acetone though barely noticeable. Lovely Sharp fruityness. Very thin and prickly on the tongue. A very enjoyable beer.

This is not an imperial stout, Im going to just it as if it were just a normal stout. Aroma of black malt, not much else. Very dark, very thin head. Roast malt with strong licorice flavors, quite enjoyable! Thin body with minimal carbonation. Overall my favorite from old main brewery.

Very malt aromas, some meanoidins, sweet. Dark copper with thin off white head. Taste is malty with strong diacetyl, quite slick mouth feel with low carbonation. Still enjoyable and quite easy drinking.

Sharpness to the aroma, hiding the caramel malt aromas. Amber in color with thin head. Flavour is fruity, more like an ale than a lager, with strong diacetyl in the finish. Low carbonation. A nice enough beer, more like an English ale than a lager though.
Passion fruit on the nose, light body with huge fruity hop presence. Easy drinking. Dangerously so.
Pours dark brown with good head retention. Floral nose, fruity hop flavour, with restrained dark malt flavour. Beautiful beer.
Huge aroma when poured, black with thin layer of foam. Dark malt and hop aromas, follow through with flavors of the same. A+
Strong citrusy hop aroma on opening. Pours a light yellow with thin head and low carbonation. Taste was light, strong hop bitterness. Enjoyable.

Nice floral aroma. Pours a cloudy orange with decent head that sticks around for the duration. Lovely sweet malt on the tongue with a good fruity hop flavour finishing with a strong bitterness. Awesome beer.

Pours dark, almost pitch black with dark tan head. Head retention is low, but it managed to maintain a thin foam throughout. Aroma is molasses and malt, light roast with a sweet coffee. Tastes a bit sharp, but a nice sweetness and toasty and roasty finish. A slight bit too carbonated for my tastes, but this definitely gives a acidic bite to what would otherwise be quite a sweet beer. Well worth drinking this!

Beautiful dark amber, highly carbonated with thin off white head. Spicy on the nose with hints of biscuit. Mild cloves and biscuit taste. Dry finish, low body with refreshing carbonation. Nice refreshing lunch time dunkel weiss.
Amber with minimal head retention. Alcohol and dried fruit on the nose. Sharp alcohol and caramel flavors, boiled sweets, strong malt. A very nice doppel bock.

Low aroma, slight bananas and cloves. Tastes of cloves with slight bubble gum with a sharp finish. Very refreshing, adequate carbonation with nice white head but low retention. Golden colour. Really nice.

Brought to us all the way from the US, this beer has traveled well. Mild fruity aroma, and a beautiful clear golden orange colour with thin head. Massive hop bitterness with good caramel sweetness to back it up. Be warned, this bitterness doesnt fade. Really enjoyable beer!
Pours a deep red with thin head. Toffee on the nose. Strong caramel notes with a good hoppyness. Very enjoyable, deceptively strong!

Pours a beautiful red with light tan head that quickly subsides to a thin foam. Aroma is sweet and fruity. Flavor is massive amounts of Crystal malt and spicy hop. Quite dry on the finish, leaves you wanting more.

Fruity esters and huge amounts of late addition hops dominates the aroma. Very clear, beautiful Amber, not great had retention though. Flavor does not seem like a 4.5% beer! Caramel, citrus, with a slightly spicy finish. Very enjoyable.
Pours hazy pale yellow, litchi on the nose. Very little head, and the carbonation is lower than expected. Refreshing and fruity, but quite light on the tongue. my first wit, quite enjoyable.
Bananas on the nose, hazy gold appearance with thin head. Not sure Ive ever tasted such a strong bubble gum flavor outside of a blue milkshake...
beer_name: Brewers & Union Beast of the Deep

review_blob: Bought as Faxe Royal Export, in a 500ml can. Wasnt expecting this to amount to much, and the initial aroma was pretty much mass produced lager, corny and not much else. Looks nice, and actually has pretty good head retention. Actually has a hint of mouth feel, and the flavour comes through as a nice light maltyness with just a hint of bitterness. Overall not a terrible mass produced lager.
Pours Amber and the citrusy hops dominate immediately. Love this beers aroma. Taste disappoints after all that aroma. Starts well, but almost immediately overrun by the bitterness.
Golden yellow with good head retention. Citrusy nose, butdoesnt jump out at me. Tastes of grapefruit and orange skin. starts sweet but a huge bitterness takes over and just wont leave.
Beautiful Brown with tan head. Aroma of coffee and toasty malt. Sharp on the tongue with strong roast and coffee. Not really my ideal porter, but tasty.

Pours dirty yellow with minimal head, which never the less sticks around till the end. Nice citrusy hop aroma which continues into the flavor. Strong bitterness finishes it off. Not sure I can taste any juniper.
Pours pitch black with minimal head. Strong chocolate aromas. Sweet on the tongue at first, with strong roast bitterness kicking in. Huge body, massive taste. A great way to end an evening.
beer_name: Dark Horse Plead the 5th Imperial Stout

review_blob: Pours black with dark tan head. So much coffee on the nose, the blueberry barely registers. Strong coffee and smoke in the taste, blueberry is subdued but begins improve with warmth. Subtle, very good.
Pours hazy orange with low head. Citrusy sweet aromas, caramelly malt and toffee under the fruit. Massive sweet alcohol on the first dip, hops comes through finishing with a very big bitterness. Wow.
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: Pours hazy orange with low head. Citrusy aromas with mild malt coming through. Flavour is sweet caramel with fruit hop flavours. Very good.
Pours hazy orange with low head. Less hop aroma than expected, but got citrus and other fruit aromas. Flavour is sweet caramel with good hop citrus. Very nice.
Pours hazy orange with low head. Grapefruit, resin and pine on the nose, and the flavour follows with more. This I could drink all day long.
Pours hazy orange with low head. Aroma starts off citrus, a swirl of the glass seems to reveal piney hints. Strong bitterness keeps this from getting too sweet.
Pours hazy orange with low head. Good fruit on the nose, not hugely raspberry, but once you drink it the raspberry comes through strong. Light body, good hop bitterness.
Whiskey aromas but sharp. Murky brown. Sour, smokey with slight banana flavor. Not finishable.
Aroma of piney resin & citrusy hops. Caramel and alcohol. Flavour is intense. Caramel sweetness gives way to a lasting bitterness. Strong body, lovely lasting impression on the tongue.
Aroma of spice and citrus and honey. Prickly carbonation, light biscuit and spice flavours. Medium Light body. Not a huge weiss drinker myself, but this I could drink lots of.
Aroma:, roasty, caramel, coffee, vanilla, sherry. Sherry / port flavours with intense sweetness fade into smokey vanilla and port. Drys from the oak. Just wow.
Aroma:citrus, caramel. Flavour starts sweet citrus drying out into a nice strong bitterness. Low body,  Very easy drinking.
